Parents, this would be great for students!

Pioneer comes to the rescue! For a limited time, Pioneer will help with the following:
All new Pioneer Internet customers will be eligible for free installation, free equipment, and two months of free service
Pioneer will waive customer deposits for new Internet customers
All Pioneer retail office locations will open our WIFI network to the public to create a free drive-up hot spot
Existing Pioneer Cellular customers will have their data overages forgiven during the crisis to ensure every customer stays connected
In addition, hot spot limitations for our Cellular customers will be temporarily removed to allow mobile devices to become WIFI hot spots for homes without broadband connectivity
Pioneer is waiving late fee penalties and has suspended all disconnects of unpaid services

FORT SUPPLY SCHOOL DISTRICT OPERATIONAL SHUTDOWN INFORMATION
MARCH 18, 2020

How will I know if school is closed or reopened?
Currently Fort Supply School District is operationally closed through April 5th, 2020. We will communicate further information and reopening notifications via our social media pages, email, bulletins posted and news.

Meals will be provided for free!
Sack breakfast and lunches will be available for pick-up only at the Fort Supply School for all students. Meal pick up times will be between 8:00- 8:30 am breakfast and 11:30 am - 12:00 pm (lunch) each weekday. No public access to buildings and no children are allowed to be left at any school site including playground.

The Department of Education will closely monitor the COVID-19 situation with state health experts to determine if it will be necessary to extend the closure. All school related activities, field trips, extracurricular activities and practices have been cancelled during this time. Fort Supply Schools will provide information to the families of our students as it becomes available.
